> This Southwest-inspired skillet supper has bold flavors that'll warm you from the inside out—there's tender rice, bites of flavorful chicken sausage, and sautéed pepper and onion. It's all topped with gooey melted pepper jack and hot sauce for a little kick, plus fresh salsa and a dollop of tangy lime crema.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and juice
from @lime{1}. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Salsa Fresca ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @Roma tomato{1}(diced), a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon},
a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and as much lime juice and lime zest as you like.

== Skillet ==

Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 4.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and sliced). Core, deseed,
and dice @long green pepper{1}(cored and diced). Zest and quarter lime.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan
over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat
into pieces, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add onion, green pepper, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until
veggies are lightly browned and sausage is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add cooked rice, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and 1/4 cup
@water{1/4%cup} to pan. Stir to thoroughly combine.

> TIP: If pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Top sausage mixture with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}. Broil until cheese is bubbly,
~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Top broiled sausage mixture with salsa and crema. Drizzle with @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if
desired. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.